==English==
===Etymology===
From Middle English, from Old English [[tunge]]. Cognates include Latin [[lingua]].
===Noun===
'''tongue''' (''plural'' '''tongues''')

#The very flexible muscle inside the [[mouth]] that is used to move food around and can be moved into various positions to modify the flow of air from the [[lung]]s in order to produce different sounds in [[speech]]. It contains the primary sensors for [[taste]].
#A [[language]].
#:''He was speaking in his native '''tongue'''.''

===Synonyms===
*(2): [[language]], [[lingo]] (''colloquial'')

